snippets.title: SecurityCenter bulkMuteFindings Sample
snippets.description: Kicks off an LRO to bulk mute findings for a parent based on a filter. The parent can be either an organization, folder or project. The findings matched by the filter will be muted after the LRO is done.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter createSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Creates a resident SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule at the scope of the given CRM parent, and also creates inherited SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules for all CRM descendants of the given parent. These modules are enabled by default.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter createSource Sample
snippets.description: Creates a source.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter createFinding Sample
snippets.description: Creates a finding. The corresponding source must exist for finding creation to succeed.

snippets.description: Deletes a notification config.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter deleteSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the specified SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule and all of its descendants in the CRM hierarchy. This method is only supported for resident custom modules.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter groupAssets Sample
snippets.description: Filters an organization's assets and  groups them by their specified properties.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter groupFindings Sample
snippets.description: Filters an organization or source's findings and  groups them by their specified properties. To group across all sources provide a `-` as the source id. Example: /v1/organizations/{organization_id}/sources/-/findings, /v1/folders/{folder_id}/sources/-/findings, /v1/projects/{project_id}/sources/-/findings

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listAssets Sample
snippets.description: Lists an organization's assets.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listDescendantSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules Sample
snippets.description: Returns a list of all resident SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules under the given CRM parent and all of the parentâ€™s CRM descendants.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listFindings Sample
snippets.description: Lists an organization or source's findings. To list across all sources provide a `-` as the source id. Example: /v1/organizations/{organization_id}/sources/-/findings

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listMuteConfigs Sample
snippets.description: Lists mute configs.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listNotificationConfigs Sample
snippets.description: Lists notification configs.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listEffectiveSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules Sample
snippets.description: Returns a list of all EffectiveSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules for the given parent. This includes resident modules defined at the scope of the parent, and inherited modules, inherited from CRM ancestors.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules Sample
snippets.description: Returns a list of all SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModules for the given parent. This includes resident modules defined at the scope of the parent, and inherited modules, inherited from CRM ancestors.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listSources Sample
snippets.description: Lists all sources belonging to an organization.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter runAssetDiscovery Sample
snippets.description: Runs asset discovery. The discovery is tracked with a long-running operation. This API can only be called with limited frequency for an organization. If it is called too frequently the caller will receive a TOO_MANY_REQUESTS error.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter setFindingState Sample
snippets.description: Updates the state of a finding.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter setMute Sample
snippets.description: Updates the mute state of a finding.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter setIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Sets the access control policy on the specified Source.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter testIamPermissions Sample
snippets.description: Returns the permissions that a caller has on the specified source.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter simulateSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Simulates a given SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule and Resource.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateExternalSystem Sample
snippets.description: Updates external system. This is for a given finding.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateFinding Sample
snippets.description: Creates or updates a finding. The corresponding source must exist for a finding creation to succeed.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateMuteConfig Sample
snippets.description: Updates a mute config.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateNotificationConfig Sample
snippets.description: Updates a notification config. The following update fields are allowed: description, pubsub_topic, streaming_config.filter

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateOrganizationSettings Sample
snippets.description: Updates an organization's settings.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateSecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Updates the SecurityHealthAnalyticsCustomModule under the given name based on the given update mask. Updating the enablement state is supported on both resident and inherited modules (though resident modules cannot have an enablement state of "inherited"). Updating the display name and custom config of a module is supported on resident modules only.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateSource Sample
snippets.description: Updates a source.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateSecurityMarks Sample
snippets.description: Updates security marks.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter createBigQueryExport Sample
snippets.description: Creates a BigQuery export.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter deleteBigQueryExport Sample
snippets.description: Deletes an existing BigQuery export.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateBigQueryExport Sample
snippets.description: Updates a BigQuery export.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listBigQueryExports Sample
snippets.description: Lists BigQuery exports. Note that when requesting BigQuery exports at a given level all exports under that level are also returned e.g. if requesting BigQuery exports under a folder, then all BigQuery exports immediately under the folder plus the ones created under the projects within the folder are returned.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter createEventThreatDetectionCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Creates a resident Event Threat Detection custom module at the scope of the given Resource Manager parent, and also creates inherited custom modules for all descendants of the given parent. These modules are enabled by default.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter deleteEventThreatDetectionCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the specified Event Threat Detection custom module and all of its descendants in the Resource Manager hierarchy. This method is only supported for resident custom modules.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter getEventThreatDetectionCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Gets an Event Threat Detection custom module.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listDescendantEventThreatDetectionCustomModules Sample
snippets.description: Lists all resident Event Threat Detection custom modules under the given Resource Manager parent and its descendants.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listEventThreatDetectionCustomModules Sample
snippets.description: Lists all Event Threat Detection custom modules for the given Resource Manager parent. This includes resident modules defined at the scope of the parent along with modules inherited from ancestors.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateEventThreatDetectionCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Updates the Event Threat Detection custom module with the given name based on the given update mask. Updating the enablement state is supported for both resident and inherited modules (though resident modules cannot have an enablement state of "inherited"). Updating the display name or configuration of a module is supported for resident modules only. The type of a module cannot be changed.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter validateEventThreatDetectionCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Validates the given Event Threat Detection custom module.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter getEffectiveEventThreatDetectionCustomModule Sample
snippets.description: Gets an effective Event Threat Detection custom module at the given level.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listEffectiveEventThreatDetectionCustomModules Sample
snippets.description: Lists all effective Event Threat Detection custom modules for the given parent. This includes resident modules defined at the scope of the parent along with modules inherited from its ancestors.

snippets.description: Creates a ResourceValueConfig for an organization. Maps user's tags to difference resource values for use by the attack path simulation.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter getResourceValueConfig Sample
snippets.description: Gets a ResourceValueConfig.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listResourceValueConfigs Sample
snippets.description: Lists all ResourceValueConfigs.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter updateResourceValueConfig Sample
snippets.description: Updates an existing ResourceValueConfigs with new rules.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listValuedResources Sample
snippets.description: Lists the valued resources for a set of simulation results and filter.

snippets.title: SecurityCenter listAttackPaths Sample
snippets.description: Lists the attack paths for a set of simulation results or valued resources and filter.
